            >
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-white"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M8 7V3m8 4V3m-9 8h10M5 21h14a2 2 0 002-2V7a2 2 0 00-2-2H5a2 2 0 00-2 2v12a2 2 0 002 2z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
              Set End Dates
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Choose when recurring meetings should end. Set a specific date,
              number of occurrences, or let them continue indefinitely until you
              manually stop them.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Feature 6 -->
        <div class="group relative">
          <div
            class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
          >
          </div>
          <div
            class="relative bg-surface/80 dark:bg-surface/50 backdrop-blur-sm border border-border hover:border-orange-500/50 rounded-3xl p-8 transition-all duration-300 hover:-translate-y-2 h-full"
          >
            <div
              class="w-16 h-16 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500 to-orange-600 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center mb-6 group-hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-300 shadow-lg shadow-orange-500/25"
            >
              <svg
                class="w-8 h-8 text-white"
                fill="none"
                viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                stroke="currentColor"
                stroke-width="2"
              >
                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M11 5H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v11a2 2 0 002 2h11a2 2 0 002-2v-5m-1.414-9.414a2 2 0 112.828 2.828L11.828 15H9v-2.828l8.586-8.586z"
                ></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
              Easy to Modify
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Update recurring meeting details anytime. Change the time,
              frequency, or end date - modifications apply to all future
              occurrences automatically.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="features-grid"
            width="32"
            height="32"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path
              d="M 32 0 L 0 0 0 32"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#features-grid)"></rect>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          What Are Recurring Meetings?
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Recurring meetings are appointments that repeat on a schedule you
            define. Instead of manually creating the same meeting every week or
            month, set it up once and CalendHub creates all the future
            occurrences automatically. Weekly team meetings, bi-weekly coaching
            sessions, monthly reviews - any meeting that happens regularly can
            be set as recurring to save time and ensure consistency.
          </p>

          <p>
            Creating recurring meetings in CalendHub is straightforward. When
            setting up a new appointment, choose the recurrence pattern that
            fits your needs: daily, weekly, monthly, or custom. Specify which
            days of the week for weekly meetings, which date of the month for
            monthly meetings, or build custom patterns like every other Tuesday.
            The system generates all future meeting instances automatically
            based on your pattern.
          </p>

          <p>
            Recurring meetings maintain the same details across all occurrences
            - same time, same duration, same participants. If you need to change
            something, update the recurring meeting settings and all future
            occurrences reflect the new details. This ensures consistency across
            your regular meetings while giving you flexibility to adjust as
            needed. Individual occurrences can also be modified or cancelled
            without affecting the entire series.
          </p>

          <p>
            CalendHub handles all the complexity of recurring meetings behind
            the scenes. The system manages timezone conversions for recurring
            meetings, ensures no conflicts with other appointments, and syncs
            all occurrences to your connected calendars automatically. Whether
            you're scheduling weekly one-on-ones, monthly all-hands meetings, or
            custom patterns for specific projects, recurring meetings save time
            and keep your regular commitments organized.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Badge -->
        <div
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-orange-500/10 border border-orange-500/20 rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-6"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-4 h-4"
            fill="none"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
          </svg>
          <span>How It Works</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Heading -->
        <h2
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 text-text"
        >
          Create Recurring Meetings
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted">In Three Simple Steps</span>
        </h2>

        <!-- 3 Step Cards -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="group relative">
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
